I always try and be as open as possible.  In forms of social media, it’s still difficult.  Facts or thoughts can be presented but even in context they still exist in a bubble.  Some people will like this photo without even reading the context. I’ve been thinking a lot about loss lately, especially having the new pup & remembering how devastated I was when my lab Trina passed away a few years ago.  I’ve had 4 friends pass away in the last year or so from various illnesses, including Robert seen here, whom I miss terribly.  Loss & mourning should never be something we are ashamed of.  I’m glad I have photographs to help memorialize these magical people.

I’ve been house bound since the weekend as I’ve been on the mend from a very bad bout of strep throat.  Had to say no to a job I really wanted to do, in a place I’ve always wanted to go to.  Yet, I’m finally learning my lesson and putting my health first, even if that’s hard to do sometimes.  For now though, I have @titusfauntleroy being my forever desert mood.
weekend mood

night vibes with one of my fave collaborators @drowanj - Nostalgia has gotten the best of me lately & I’ve been thinking a lot about my move to LA.  As much as I’ve loved the transition it’s still been very hard. 34 years of cultivating relationships and a life in NY, I can’t help but feel disconnected quite often.  Then I look at photographs like this to help me. I can tangibly feel what a special day this was, hear the rushes of wind from the beach & remember home is wherever you want it to be.
